{
  "texts": [
    "42 Language models (2018 onwards): The most recent models rely on deep learning.",
    "They also excel in analysing the whole document, but here the vectors are dynamic and adapt to the context.",
    "Transformer models are able to understand the difference when the same word is used in different contexts.",
    "43 -Large language models rely on deep neural networks, which are better at detecting and predicting ''complicated linguistic structures along with their long-distance relationships, as humans do''.",
    "44 Another difference of transformers is that they can process words ''in parallel'', instead of ''sequentially one by one'' like the former methods."
  ]
}